WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:32.720 --> 00:35.280
And on that point,
members of the jury...

00:35.400 --> 00:37.391
...I rest my case.

00:56.080 --> 00:58.833
<i>(camera shutter clicks)</i>

01:01.920 --> 01:03.273
<i>(alarm clock rings)</i>

01:29.080 --> 01:31.036
Hello, Wanda.

02:40.480 --> 02:41.833
Hi, Ken.

02:41.960 --> 02:43.109
Hello, W-W-Wanda.

02:44.080 --> 02:45.433
Ken...

02:46.360 --> 02:47.315
...this is Otto.

02:47.440 --> 02:49.954
Hello, Ken.
Wanda's told me a lot about you.

02:50.080 --> 02:51.195
Hey! Great fish!

02:52.400 --> 02:55.437
A squeeze of lemon,
some tartare sauce... perfect!

02:56.360 --> 02:58.032
George back yet?

02:58.160 --> 03:00.071
No, he had to g-g-go...

03:00.200 --> 03:02.430
...to the b-b-b...

03:05.080 --> 03:06.115
What?

03:06.240 --> 03:09.676
That's quite a stutter you've got there,
Ken.

03:09.800 --> 03:12.394
<i>(laughs)</i>
It's all right, it doesn't bother me.

03:12.520 --> 03:15.114
So er...
George needs a weapons man, eh?

03:16.080 --> 03:17.035
A cup of tea, Ken?

03:17.160 --> 03:18.957
Y-y-y...

03:19.080 --> 03:20.638
Yeah, he'd like one.

03:20.760 --> 03:23.320
I had a good friend in the CIA,
had a stutter.

03:23.440 --> 03:24.953
Cost him his life, dammit.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.513
<i>(door opens)</i>

03:28.080 --> 03:29.832
Hi, George.

03:31.080 --> 03:32.877
Hello, George.

03:33.000 --> 03:34.069
Get you a Scotch?

03:34.200 --> 03:35.758
Yeah.

03:35.880 --> 03:36.835
George...

03:38.080 --> 03:39.433
...this is Otto.

03:40.640 --> 03:41.993
So...

03:42.120 --> 03:43.792
...you're Wanda's brother?

03:43.920 --> 03:45.319
Good to be here, George.

03:45.440 --> 03:47.158
England is a fine country.

03:47.280 --> 03:49.032
Did she tell you what we need?

03:54.080 --> 03:55.035
<i>(Ken gasps)</i>

03:57.880 --> 03:59.632
<i>(Otto)</i> Something like that?

04:02.080 --> 04:04.036
Something like that.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.033
Hello, Wendy.

04:09.480 --> 04:10.674
Had a good day?

04:11.520 --> 04:14.671
I spend the morning
<i>trying</i> to get a waste disposal man.

04:14.800 --> 04:18.110
At lunch, Marjorie just
complained about her husband...

04:18.240 --> 04:21.072
...then I have to play
<i>three</i> rubbers with Philippa.

04:21.200 --> 04:23.998
I come back and
Sandersons have sent the wrong flowers.

04:24.120 --> 04:25.633
Oh, no!

04:26.920 --> 04:28.478
Would you like some tea?

04:29.480 --> 04:30.674
Yes.

04:31.880 --> 04:33.359
I won the case.

04:33.480 --> 04:36.790
This is the first moment
I've had to myself all day.

04:40.160 --> 04:42.037
Hello, Portia! How was the show?

04:42.160 --> 04:44.355
Awful, Daddy. I must have a new horse.

04:44.480 --> 04:47.438
- But you liked Phantom.
- He's not fit for dog meat.

04:47.560 --> 04:49.630
Can I change him? It won't cost much.

04:49.760 --> 04:52.228
- Oughtn't we...
- I thought you were making tea.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.794
- I am, darling. Sorry.
- I'd better get it.

04:54.920 --> 04:57.150
- No, no, let me do it.
- No! I'll do it!

05:00.280 --> 05:01.633
I won the case.

05:01.760 --> 05:03.796
Now this is cracked.

05:05.280 --> 05:08.192
They're worth about 100,000 each.

05:08.680 --> 05:10.432
There are 135 of them.

05:10.560 --> 05:13.028
That makes 13 millions, my friends.

05:13.160 --> 05:14.275
Dollars or pounds?

05:14.400 --> 05:15.355
Pounds, pet.

05:15.480 --> 05:17.232
This is the big one. So...

05:19.480 --> 05:21.357
OK.

05:21.480 --> 05:23.550
Yeah.

05:23.680 --> 05:25.557
Otto?

05:25.680 --> 05:26.908
Yes?

05:27.040 --> 05:28.268
OK?

05:28.400 --> 05:29.355
What?

05:29.480 --> 05:30.595
The plan.

05:31.080 --> 05:32.718
Yeah. Great. No problem.

05:33.440 --> 05:36.159
What was the middle thing,
about the police?

05:37.440 --> 05:40.273
We don't meet up
at Heathrow until Tuesday...

05:40.400 --> 05:40.912
Yeah, yeah!

05:41.040 --> 05:42.871
I haven't finished yet.

05:43.000 --> 05:46.675
Because the police will watch
all the airports for 72 hours.

05:46.800 --> 05:47.676
I know.

05:47.800 --> 05:48.755
I know.

05:49.960 --> 05:52.428
Do you want me to g-g-get...

05:52.560 --> 05:54.835
...a b-b-big...

05:54.960 --> 05:57.918
...c- c-car?

05:58.040 --> 05:59.359
Getaway?

05:59.480 --> 06:00.833
A limo, OK?

06:00.960 --> 06:02.916
And put diplomatic plates on it.

06:03.040 --> 06:05.349
What if he has to speak in the break-in?

06:05.480 --> 06:07.914
Nobody says anything during a break-in.

06:08.040 --> 06:09.632
It's OK, Otto. Ken's good.

06:11.080 --> 06:13.036
So, next week...

06:13.160 --> 06:15.116
...we won't have to look for work.

06:15.240 --> 06:17.231
And it won't have to look for us.

06:18.280 --> 06:20.236
Oscar Wilde.

06:24.600 --> 06:27.068
You really like animals, don't you, Ken?

06:27.200 --> 06:28.872
What's the attraction?

06:29.000 --> 06:30.592
Because you can t-t-t...

06:30.720 --> 06:34.030
...trust them, and they don't sh-sh-sh...

06:34.160 --> 06:35.229
Shit on you?

06:35.360 --> 06:37.669
Show off all the time.

06:37.800 --> 06:40.109
You know what Nietzsche
said about them?

06:40.240 --> 06:42.629
He said they were God's second blunder.

06:42.760 --> 06:43.909
Bye, sis!

06:44.400 --> 06:47.790
Well, you tell him from me that I-I-I...

06:48.600 --> 06:49.828
Bye, George.

06:50.680 --> 06:53.035
If you talk to Mom, tell her I said hi.

06:53.160 --> 06:55.116
- OK.
- (Don't let him touch you.)

06:55.240 --> 06:57.276
One more day, and we're together.

07:00.320 --> 07:02.356
I'm sorry about my brother, Ken.

07:02.480 --> 07:03.993
I know he's insensitive.

07:04.880 --> 07:06.518
He's had a hard life.

07:06.640 --> 07:07.993
Dad used to beat him up.

07:12.080 --> 07:13.593
Good.

07:13.720 --> 07:14.675
Aaagh!

07:14.960 --> 07:16.951
<i>(screaming)</i>

08:35.080 --> 08:37.035
Anybody moves and you're dead.

08:57.920 --> 08:59.956
<i>(alarm rings)</i>

09:04.000 --> 09:05.956
<i>(dogs yap)</i>

09:07.080 --> 09:08.957
Look where you're going!

09:09.080 --> 09:10.638
Chauvinist pig!

09:10.760 --> 09:14.070
Really, people here
just think they own the pavement.

09:17.120 --> 09:18.314
<i>(engine starts)</i>

09:22.000 --> 09:24.070
<i>(brakes screech)</i>

09:41.080 --> 09:42.229
That was fun.

09:42.360 --> 09:43.998
I love robbing the English.

09:44.120 --> 09:46.156
- They're so polite.
- The d-d-d...

09:46.280 --> 09:47.838
- What is it, Ken?
- The dog!

09:47.960 --> 09:49.188
We didn't hit the dog.

09:49.320 --> 09:52.949
- $20 million and an insect worries him!
- It's not an in-in...

09:53.080 --> 09:56.231
Stutter's not getting any better.
How about surgery?

09:56.360 --> 09:57.315
<i>(George)</i> Shut up!

09:57.440 --> 09:58.759
<i>(siren)</i>

10:03.160 --> 10:04.434
Ken.

10:06.080 --> 10:07.035
Bye!

10:37.480 --> 10:38.595
Let's split.

10:38.720 --> 10:42.156
- See you at Heathrow on Tuesday.
- Lie low. No celebrating.

10:42.280 --> 10:43.713
No celebrating?

10:44.480 --> 10:46.072
See you in a couple of hours.

11:33.560 --> 11:34.709
To $20 million.

11:34.840 --> 11:35.909
To a job well done.

11:36.040 --> 11:36.995
To us.

11:37.120 --> 11:39.839
To the best
brother and sister team since...

11:39.960 --> 11:41.029
Romeo and Juliet?

11:41.480 --> 11:44.836
Do you believe those Cockney klutzes
bought our story?

11:44.960 --> 11:45.915
What morons!

11:46.040 --> 11:48.270
- I want you to know something.
- What?

11:48.400 --> 11:51.710
Even if you were my brother,
I'd still want to fuck you.

11:51.840 --> 11:52.795
Oooh!

11:54.480 --> 11:55.959
Make the call.

11:56.080 --> 11:57.638
- Momento, carissima.
- No!

11:57.760 --> 11:59.273
- Eventuale!
- No Italian!

11:59.400 --> 12:00.355
Hey!

12:00.480 --> 12:03.677
Per cominciare,
due insalate verdi con peperoni.

12:03.800 --> 12:06.268
- E linguine primavera...
- No. No.

12:06.400 --> 12:09.437
- Una cotoletta di vitello.
- Make the call, Otto.

12:09.560 --> 12:10.993
Are you really Italian?

12:11.120 --> 12:12.599
Absolutamente. Si!

12:12.720 --> 12:14.517
My name is Otto. It means eight.

12:14.640 --> 12:16.232
Say arrivederci a Giorgio.

12:16.360 --> 12:17.270
Bye, George.

12:17.400 --> 12:19.311
<i>(ltalian accent)</i> The police, please.

12:19.440 --> 12:21.032
Otto!

12:22.080 --> 12:23.957
<i>(English accent)</i> Yes, hello.

12:24.080 --> 12:27.038
Sorry to trouble you,
but you may like to know...

12:27.160 --> 12:32.188
...that today's Hatton Garden robbery
was pulled off by Mr George Thomason.

12:32.320 --> 12:35.835
He lives at flat three, Kipling Mansions...

12:35.960 --> 12:39.270
...Murray Road, London W9.

12:40.040 --> 12:41.189
Wanda!

12:51.560 --> 12:53.516
<i>(siren)</i>

13:03.480 --> 13:05.755
<i>(banging on door)</i> Police! Open up!

13:06.640 --> 13:08.278
Come on, open up!

13:12.520 --> 13:14.988
Open the door, or we'll knock it down!

13:24.840 --> 13:26.592
George Francis Thomason?

13:38.280 --> 13:39.633
Passport...

13:39.760 --> 13:40.909
...tickets...

13:41.040 --> 13:41.995
...money!

13:46.480 --> 13:47.833
<i>(honks horn)</i>

13:47.960 --> 13:49.598
<i>(Otto)</i> Asshole!

13:49.720 --> 13:51.358
<i>(crashing)</i>

13:59.240 --> 14:00.832
We're rich, Wanda.

14:00.960 --> 14:02.029
Yep?

14:02.160 --> 14:03.798
I bet these weeks with me...

14:03.920 --> 14:06.798
...have been
the most exciting weeks of your life.

14:06.920 --> 14:08.069
You said it.

14:17.920 --> 14:19.911
<i>(breathes deeply)</i>

14:20.480 --> 14:21.435
<i>(calmly)</i> OK.

14:22.080 --> 14:23.832
OK.

14:23.960 --> 14:25.439
Disappointed!

14:26.880 --> 14:28.233
Sonofabitch!

14:29.080 --> 14:31.640
What do you have to do
to make people trust you?!

14:31.760 --> 14:33.034
Shut up.

14:33.160 --> 14:35.720
People are always
taking advantage of me!

14:35.840 --> 14:38.035
Shut up and think.
Where's he moved it?

14:40.880 --> 14:41.869
What are you doing?

14:42.000 --> 14:43.956
I'm thinking!

14:44.080 --> 14:45.832
Thinking what I'll do to him.

14:45.960 --> 14:47.996
I'll hang him up with piano wire...

14:48.120 --> 14:51.078
- Where are you going?
- I'm going to talk to him.

14:51.880 --> 14:53.029
Talk to who?

14:53.480 --> 14:54.595
Talk to who?!

14:54.720 --> 14:57.553
So, while installing these windows...

14:57.680 --> 15:01.309
...you knelt on some broken glass
from the pane you had dropped.

15:01.440 --> 15:02.589
That's right, sir.

15:02.720 --> 15:04.597
Your parents can confirm this?

15:04.720 --> 15:05.994
Yes, and his aunt...

15:06.120 --> 15:07.633
...Georgina Thomason.

15:07.760 --> 15:08.749
Good, Bartlett.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.233
- <i>(knock at door)</i>
- Yes?

15:11.000 --> 15:12.752
Sorry to interrupt you, sir.

15:12.880 --> 15:14.950
Thomason. A young lady to see you.

15:15.080 --> 15:18.311
- Anything else?
- No, thanks. Do you have to dash off?

15:18.440 --> 15:19.759
No, absolutely not.

15:19.880 --> 15:20.835
George!

15:20.960 --> 15:23.520
Ken's got the fish food. He'll be in later.

15:23.640 --> 15:24.789
- Thanks.
- De nada.

15:24.920 --> 15:26.592
What do you think, Mr Leach?

15:26.720 --> 15:30.713
We may be OK on the glass,
but what else will they come up with?

15:34.880 --> 15:35.949
<i>(wolf whistling)</i>

15:41.040 --> 15:42.792
Oh, George!

15:42.920 --> 15:45.639
Oh, my God, I can't believe
this is happening.

15:45.760 --> 15:47.671
That's not allowed in here, miss.

15:47.800 --> 15:48.949
Are you OK?

15:49.080 --> 15:50.229
It's all right.

15:50.360 --> 15:52.237
I don't think I can handle this.

15:52.360 --> 15:54.715
I was too afraid to sleep last night...

15:54.840 --> 15:56.637
Leave it out, leave it out, OK?

15:57.680 --> 15:59.398
Listen, listen, listen.

15:59.520 --> 16:00.999
Listen.

16:02.080 --> 16:04.036
You stayed at my place.

16:05.080 --> 16:06.991
We slept late.

16:07.120 --> 16:09.076
You made me breakfast.

16:13.280 --> 16:15.032
What?

16:15.160 --> 16:17.037
What's he doing here?

16:17.160 --> 16:19.037
He wanted to see you.

16:19.680 --> 16:21.796
Who did it, George? Kevin Delaney?

16:21.920 --> 16:23.876
Do you want me to rub him out?

16:24.000 --> 16:25.956
Anything, you name it.

16:26.080 --> 16:28.355
I have friends making enquiries.

16:28.480 --> 16:30.038
Good.

16:30.160 --> 16:32.754
The jewels are very safe.

16:32.880 --> 16:36.589
If I get sent down, it all gets
handed back to cut my sentence.

16:36.720 --> 16:38.995
Now, to cut my sentence even more...

16:39.120 --> 16:41.475
...I could tell them who done it with me...

16:41.600 --> 16:44.239
...if I wasn't very happy about everything.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.797
What was the middle thing?

16:47.920 --> 16:49.876
Piss off.

16:53.480 --> 16:55.835
- You want me to spring you...
- Now!

17:00.880 --> 17:02.233
George?

17:03.480 --> 17:05.038
You don't think...

17:05.160 --> 17:06.718
Do you?

17:06.839 --> 17:07.795
No!

17:11.040 --> 17:11.994
No.

17:12.880 --> 17:14.154
No!

17:14.280 --> 17:16.077
OK.

17:16.200 --> 17:17.189
- George.
- What?

17:19.240 --> 17:21.674
Are you sure the garage is very safe?

17:23.720 --> 17:25.438
Trust me.

17:25.560 --> 17:27.311
Thank you very much.

17:27.440 --> 17:28.953
Thanks a lot. Bye.

17:29.080 --> 17:30.229
Have a good day.

17:31.320 --> 17:32.275
So?

17:32.400 --> 17:33.799
He's not sure it was you.

17:33.920 --> 17:34.875
What about you?

17:35.000 --> 17:36.353
No, no, he believes me.

17:36.480 --> 17:38.835
That's why he can't figure out about you.

17:38.960 --> 17:39.949
Figure out what?

17:40.080 --> 17:42.548
Whether you turned him in or not, stupid!

17:43.480 --> 17:45.436
Don't er...

17:45.560 --> 17:48.233
...ever, ever, <i>ever...</i>

17:48.360 --> 17:49.952
...call me stupid. OK?

17:52.400 --> 17:53.355
What?

17:56.960 --> 17:58.598
That's George's lawyer.

17:59.480 --> 18:01.675
The other guy must be the barrister.

18:03.440 --> 18:04.395
So?

18:04.520 --> 18:05.635
Trust me.

18:09.120 --> 18:11.509
Let me know
if anything unexpected turns...

18:11.640 --> 18:12.834
Excuse me.

18:12.960 --> 18:14.598
Don't I recognise you?

18:15.680 --> 18:17.716
No. No, I don't think so.

18:17.840 --> 18:19.432
Oh.

18:19.560 --> 18:21.949
You are a famous barrister, aren't you?

18:22.480 --> 18:23.833
Erm...

18:23.960 --> 18:25.916
Well, hardly.

18:26.040 --> 18:28.315
Could I have your autograph, anyway?

18:30.280 --> 18:31.599
Yes, yes, certainly.

18:31.720 --> 18:32.675
Thanks.

18:32.800 --> 18:35.519
I'm studying aspects of your legal system.

18:35.640 --> 18:36.595
I'm American.

18:36.720 --> 18:37.675
Oh, really?

18:37.800 --> 18:40.439
I've only just started. It's fascinating.

18:40.560 --> 18:42.516
What er... What brings you here?

18:42.640 --> 18:44.596
Oh, it's a little embarrassing.

18:44.720 --> 18:46.676
I... have a friend.

18:46.800 --> 18:48.028
Oh!

18:48.160 --> 18:49.115
I see.

18:49.240 --> 18:50.275
There you are.

18:50.400 --> 18:51.355
I knew it!

18:51.480 --> 18:52.993
You're Archie <i>Leash.</i>

18:53.120 --> 18:54.075
Leach.

18:54.200 --> 18:55.235
Right.

18:55.360 --> 18:56.759
I saw you in court!

18:56.880 --> 18:58.836
Er... two weeks ago.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.234
The casino break-in?

19:00.360 --> 19:01.918
You were great!

19:02.040 --> 19:03.996
Oh, I'm a big fan of yours.

19:04.120 --> 19:05.872
I love the way you er...

19:06.000 --> 19:07.433
...cross-examine.

19:08.440 --> 19:10.829
Oh, I really admire your work.

19:10.960 --> 19:11.915
Thank you.

19:14.080 --> 19:16.150
- I'd better not...
- I don't suppose...

19:16.280 --> 19:18.236
No? Fine, right.

19:18.360 --> 19:19.315
Well...

19:19.440 --> 19:20.953
Thank you for this.

19:21.080 --> 19:22.354
I'll treasure it.

19:24.640 --> 19:26.756
Au revoir.

19:28.680 --> 19:30.432
You speak French, too!

19:49.800 --> 19:51.472
What's going on?

19:51.600 --> 19:54.990
Whatever George decides to do,
he'll tell Leach first.

19:55.120 --> 19:56.473
Why?

19:56.600 --> 19:58.113
Because he's his lawyer.

19:58.240 --> 19:59.309
Yeah, I know that.

19:59.440 --> 20:01.556
So I'm going to get to know Mr Leach.

20:01.800 --> 20:04.678
So George will tell <i>him</i>
where the diamonds are?

20:04.800 --> 20:06.995
That's what I'm going to find out.

20:18.640 --> 20:19.914
You done well, my son.

20:20.920 --> 20:23.115
Now, where are we going to hide it?

20:25.280 --> 20:26.429
<i>(inaudible)</i>

20:26.560 --> 20:27.959
Very good!

20:28.080 --> 20:29.752
Don't tell Wanda anything.

20:29.880 --> 20:32.030
Otto might get something out of her.

20:32.160 --> 20:33.115
Now...

20:33.240 --> 20:34.832
George.

20:34.960 --> 20:36.712
You are going to g-get off?

20:36.840 --> 20:38.796
Sure, don't worry about it, Ken.

20:38.920 --> 20:39.875
We'll fix it.

20:40.000 --> 20:41.479
Now, anything on Otto?

20:41.600 --> 20:43.397
No. Not yet.

20:44.480 --> 20:46.232
You watch him.

20:48.480 --> 20:50.072
Ken!

20:51.880 --> 20:53.029
OK.

20:53.480 --> 20:56.233
Looks like the police have been all over it.

20:56.360 --> 20:59.238
Let me change clothes,
then I'll help you look.

21:00.080 --> 21:01.832
<i>(English accent)</i> Hello...

21:01.960 --> 21:03.996
...K- K-Ken's p-p-pets.

21:04.840 --> 21:05.636
Hey!

21:06.680 --> 21:08.432
Wake up!

21:08.560 --> 21:09.834
Wake up, limey fish!

21:12.080 --> 21:15.390
So. How are you going to get friendly
with this lawyer?

21:15.520 --> 21:17.511
I don't know. I'll improvise.

21:18.080 --> 21:19.433
Fucking insects!

21:19.560 --> 21:23.235
I thought Englishmen didn't like women,
the way they talk.

21:23.360 --> 21:24.429
No!

21:24.560 --> 21:29.076
He's straight. He's kinda cute, too,
in a pompous sort of way.

21:29.200 --> 21:30.952
Have you got the hots for him?

21:31.080 --> 21:33.674
I'm not into necrophilia, thanks.

21:33.800 --> 21:35.153
<i>(laughs)</i>

21:35.280 --> 21:37.669
What is this? Hump-a-limey week?

