28:00.080 --> 28:01.957
Davidson!

28:02.080 --> 28:05.390
An American legal student
wants to see me for a moment.

28:05.520 --> 28:07.909
- What time is Sir John due?
- 12.30, sir.

28:08.040 --> 28:08.995
Right.

28:18.480 --> 28:19.833
Come in!

28:20.880 --> 28:22.757
- Hi.
- How very nice to see you.

28:22.880 --> 28:24.711
Am I interrupting?

28:24.840 --> 28:26.273
Absolutely not.

28:26.400 --> 28:27.355
Really?

28:27.480 --> 28:29.277
Really. Delighted to see you.

28:29.400 --> 28:30.355
Hello.

28:33.480 --> 28:34.435
So.

28:35.080 --> 28:36.433
This is the place.

28:36.560 --> 28:37.629
- This is it.
- Very nice.

28:38.840 --> 28:41.991
I was at the courts this morning.
It's fascinating!

28:42.120 --> 28:43.758
Really, so much to know,

28:43.880 --> 28:45.836
Everybody wears these. Do you?

28:46.080 --> 28:47.877
- Oh, ridiculous!
<i>- (giggles)</i>

28:51.080 --> 28:52.035
Well, erm...

28:52.160 --> 28:54.230
...I only have a few minutes. Sorry.

28:54.360 --> 28:55.315
I'm sorry.

28:55.440 --> 28:58.000
But until then,
I'm all yours, as they say.

28:58.120 --> 29:00.156
I just have a couple of questions.

29:01.000 --> 29:02.956
I'm having a little problem...

29:03.080 --> 29:06.231
...understanding
preliminary criminal procedures.

29:07.080 --> 29:09.514
What exactly is the committal?

29:09.640 --> 29:10.709
Ah. Interesting.

29:10.840 --> 29:13.912
Basically,
it's a preliminary investigation...

29:14.040 --> 29:16.679
...where the prosecution
presents evidence...

29:16.800 --> 29:19.030
...that the accused has a case to answer.

29:19.160 --> 29:21.037
That's what it says in the book.

29:21.160 --> 29:24.118
Let's take, for example,
my friend George Thomason.

29:24.240 --> 29:25.389
Right.

29:25.560 --> 29:28.438
- His committal is on Wednesday...
- Thomason?

29:28.800 --> 29:29.755
Yes.

29:29.880 --> 29:30.949
George Thomason?

29:31.880 --> 29:33.598
Yes. Do you know him?

29:35.400 --> 29:36.833
I'm defending him.

29:36.960 --> 29:38.678
What are you talking about?

29:38.800 --> 29:40.791
I'm his barrister, his lawyer.

29:42.240 --> 29:43.639
That's so great!

29:45.080 --> 29:47.150
That's so weird, isn't that weird?

29:47.280 --> 29:50.511
Oh, I'm so happy you're defending him!

29:50.640 --> 29:51.595
Thank you.

29:51.720 --> 29:53.517
He's sure to get off now.

29:54.480 --> 29:55.833
Wow!

29:56.480 --> 29:58.038
I can watch you work now!

29:58.160 --> 29:59.752
Please.

30:01.960 --> 30:02.949
Amazing.

30:03.080 --> 30:04.274
Well, anyway.

30:04.400 --> 30:07.153
At the committal,
George would then plead...

30:07.280 --> 30:08.952
Not guilty.

30:09.080 --> 30:10.069
Really?

30:10.200 --> 30:13.078
The evidence is largely circumstantial.

30:13.200 --> 30:15.555
But wasn't there an identification?

30:15.680 --> 30:17.511
True, but a very elderly lady.

30:17.640 --> 30:19.710
I think they've got the wrong man.

30:21.480 --> 30:23.232
You don't think he did it?

30:23.360 --> 30:24.315
No.

30:24.440 --> 30:26.829
Let's just say, for argument's sake...

30:26.960 --> 30:28.712
...that you did think he did it.

30:28.840 --> 30:31.877
Sure, if more evidence
against him came to light.

30:32.000 --> 30:32.955
Right, right.

30:33.080 --> 30:36.277
You would then advise him
to plead guilty...

30:36.400 --> 30:40.075
...and turn over the jewels
to get his sentence cut.

30:40.200 --> 30:42.668
And he would turn them over
to who, to you?

30:44.680 --> 30:46.318
Theoretically, yes, yes.

30:46.440 --> 30:47.395
Oh, of course.

30:47.520 --> 30:48.589
Erm. Well er...

30:50.080 --> 30:53.311
I'm so sorry, I've forgotten your name.

30:55.040 --> 30:55.995
Wanda.

30:56.120 --> 30:57.997
Wanda! What a fool, what a fool.

30:58.120 --> 31:00.076
Well, Wanda, there are three...

31:05.160 --> 31:06.434
Not Wanda Gershwitz?

31:06.560 --> 31:08.437
Yes.

31:08.560 --> 31:10.357
Oh, my God.

31:10.480 --> 31:11.469
What?

31:11.600 --> 31:12.749
You're his alibi.

31:12.880 --> 31:14.871
I can't talk to you!

31:15.000 --> 31:15.955
Why not?

31:16.080 --> 31:18.435
My dear lady, you're a defence witness!

31:18.560 --> 31:20.596
I'm sorry, I must ask you to leave.

31:20.720 --> 31:22.278
What did I say?

31:22.400 --> 31:24.960
It's not ethical for me
to talk to a witness.

31:25.080 --> 31:26.991
Everybody does it in America.

31:27.120 --> 31:28.758
Not in England, it's forbidden.

31:28.920 --> 31:31.275
I insist, or I may have
to give up the case.

31:31.400 --> 31:33.356
I'm sorry. Please.

31:37.800 --> 31:39.472
Oh, Archie.

31:41.400 --> 31:45.439
I didn't come here to talk about
boring criminal procedures.

31:47.480 --> 31:49.232
Come on, you know!

31:50.720 --> 31:52.915
You knew the minute I walked in here.

31:54.880 --> 31:56.518
I want you.

31:59.080 --> 32:00.308
What?

32:00.800 --> 32:02.358
<i>(intercom buzzes)</i>

32:02.480 --> 32:04.152
- Hello?
<i>- Sir John is here.</i>

32:04.280 --> 32:05.429
Show him in, please.

32:05.560 --> 32:07.232
Make love with me.

32:07.360 --> 32:08.952
<i>- Pardon?</i>
- Nothing.

32:09.080 --> 32:11.640
- Will you take me to bed?
- No, sorry.

32:14.320 --> 32:15.799
Bye, Uncle.

32:20.000 --> 32:21.831
Hi!

32:32.000 --> 32:33.991
<i>(rousing music)</i>

32:38.080 --> 32:40.196
He's pleading not guilty...

32:40.320 --> 32:42.436
...so you're safe until the trial.

32:43.080 --> 32:44.991
Leach doesn't think he did it.

32:47.080 --> 32:49.640
Ken says
there's a safe deposit box key...

32:49.760 --> 32:52.115
...but only George knows where it is.

32:52.760 --> 32:54.034
Thank you, Wanda(!)

32:57.400 --> 32:59.356
What have <i>you</i> found out?

32:59.480 --> 33:00.674
Not a lot.

33:00.800 --> 33:02.950
You realise he's in court tomorrow?

33:03.080 --> 33:04.229
I know that!

33:04.360 --> 33:05.759
So nothing, huh?

33:05.880 --> 33:06.835
Nix.

33:07.840 --> 33:09.034
Zip.

33:09.160 --> 33:10.639
Diddly.

33:10.760 --> 33:12.193
Bupkiss.

33:14.320 --> 33:15.594
Niente.

33:20.080 --> 33:21.229
Oh, it's too big!

33:21.360 --> 33:23.669
- No, it isn't, Portia.
- It's enormous!

33:23.800 --> 33:25.950
- No, it isn't!
- Oh, please, Mother!

33:26.080 --> 33:27.638
No! Absolutely not!

33:27.760 --> 33:30.228
I'm so miserable
and you just don't care!

33:30.360 --> 33:31.509
Do shut up, Portia!

33:32.880 --> 33:35.872
All I get, all day,
is people complaining to me.

33:36.000 --> 33:37.877
Oh dear.

33:45.360 --> 33:47.316
Ecco I'uomo.

34:02.720 --> 34:06.633
Ooh, le due cupole grandi
della cattedrale di Milano.

34:50.080 --> 34:51.911
Benito Mussolini!

35:04.480 --> 35:06.311
Dov'ê il Vaticano?

35:08.720 --> 35:09.675
<i>(mutters)</i>

35:20.680 --> 35:22.591
<i># Volare</i>

35:22.720 --> 35:24.358
<i># Oh-oh</i>

35:24.480 --> 35:26.675
<i># E cantare</i>

35:26.800 --> 35:27.755
<i># Oh-oh...</i>

35:38.560 --> 35:42.030
Archie, I want <i>you</i> to speak to her
about plastic surgery.

35:42.880 --> 35:45.348
- Hmm?
- I do wish you'd listen to me.

35:45.480 --> 35:47.232
I want you to speak to Portia.

35:47.360 --> 35:49.555
I'll speak to her in the morning.

35:49.680 --> 35:51.033
Goodnight, Archie.

35:52.080 --> 35:53.752
Goodnight, Archie!

35:54.280 --> 35:55.998
Goodnight, Wanda.

35:56.480 --> 35:57.833
Goodnight, who?

35:59.080 --> 36:02.629
Sorry, darling.
Just a stupid case I've got tomorrow...

36:02.760 --> 36:04.716
...with some lousy old hag.

36:04.840 --> 36:07.832
Are you George Francis Thomason...

36:07.960 --> 36:10.520
...of Kipling Mansions, Murray Avenue...

36:10.640 --> 36:11.834
...London W9?

36:13.280 --> 36:14.474
Yes, sir.

36:14.600 --> 36:17.478
The charge is one of armed robbery.

36:17.600 --> 36:19.716
Are we ready for a committal,
Mr Percival?

36:19.840 --> 36:23.230
Yes, under Section 6.2, madam.

36:23.360 --> 36:24.634
That is correct, 6.2.

36:24.760 --> 36:28.150
Here are the statements,
all to be fully bound, please.

36:29.160 --> 36:31.071
Stand up, Mr Thomason.

36:31.200 --> 36:33.475
You are committed to stand trial...

36:33.600 --> 36:36.160
...at the Central Criminal Court.

36:36.280 --> 36:38.635
There is some urgency about this case.

36:38.760 --> 36:40.512
The main witness, Mrs Coady...

36:40.640 --> 36:44.838
...is elderly and has had
serious heart difficulties recently.

36:44.960 --> 36:47.758
Is there any possibility
that this case...

36:47.880 --> 36:50.155
...might be put down for an early trial?

36:50.280 --> 36:52.748
That is for the Old Bailey listing officer.

36:52.880 --> 36:55.952
Take him down to the cell, please, officer.

37:14.680 --> 37:16.272
Hi, hon. How are you doing?

37:16.400 --> 37:18.391
You look great. I love your hair.

37:18.520 --> 37:19.839
Got time for a coffee?

37:19.960 --> 37:22.269
- No, I've g-g...
- Have you thought about it?

37:22.400 --> 37:23.833
Why did he give you this?

37:23.960 --> 37:25.996
<i>Eileen Coady, 69 Basil Street.</i>

37:26.120 --> 37:28.634
Does he want you to send her flowers?

37:28.760 --> 37:29.749
Do her shopping?

37:29.880 --> 37:31.074
Show her a good time?

37:31.200 --> 37:33.031
Rub her out?

37:36.080 --> 37:38.036
He wants you to rub her out?

37:39.760 --> 37:41.273
He's going to kill her!

37:41.400 --> 37:42.276
<i>(laughs)</i>

37:44.480 --> 37:46.357
Fuck off, or I'll kill you.

37:46.880 --> 37:47.949
Limey fruits!

37:49.880 --> 37:52.758
So the old lady will
m-meet with an accident?

37:52.880 --> 37:54.950
- Eh, K-K-Ken?
- Sssh. Sssh!

37:55.080 --> 37:57.036
<i>(laughs)</i>

37:57.160 --> 37:58.673
What's so funny?

37:58.800 --> 38:02.031
Nothing.
Just that wasting old ladies isn't nice.

38:02.160 --> 38:05.197
Well, it's better than b-buggering people.

38:05.920 --> 38:07.911
I bet you £1 you don't kill her.

38:09.400 --> 38:10.355
All right.

38:10.800 --> 38:11.755
All right.

38:12.560 --> 38:14.949
I love watching your ass when you walk.

38:15.080 --> 38:16.672
Is that beautiful or what?

38:17.960 --> 38:19.439
Don't go near him!

38:19.560 --> 38:21.073
He's mine!

38:21.960 --> 38:24.030
£1 says you won't kill her!

38:24.160 --> 38:25.991
<i>(laughs)</i>

38:27.280 --> 38:28.759
When could you look at it?

38:28.880 --> 38:32.316
Let's think.
My wife's going to the opera on Friday.

38:32.440 --> 38:35.238
I'll look at it then
and call you on Saturday.

38:35.360 --> 38:37.669
- I really appreciate it. Thanks.
- Bye.

38:37.800 --> 38:38.755
Hi.

38:39.200 --> 38:41.156
I know we're not allowed to talk.

38:41.280 --> 38:42.508
Give me a call.

38:42.640 --> 38:43.789
I can't.

38:45.080 --> 38:46.035
Please?

38:46.160 --> 38:48.151
We're not allowed to speak.

38:48.280 --> 38:49.838
We don't have to.

38:50.880 --> 38:54.589
I don't want you for your conversation.

38:57.680 --> 38:59.511
I'd love to...

39:04.160 --> 39:06.116
<i>(wails)</i>

39:07.840 --> 39:09.956
<i>(continues howling)</i>

39:10.680 --> 39:12.955
- What happened?
- Got a date, Friday.

39:14.400 --> 39:15.150
<i>(whistles)</i>

39:27.240 --> 39:28.832
<i>(dogs yap)</i>

39:28.960 --> 39:30.439
Look here!

39:30.560 --> 39:33.199
Do you mind
not making that terrible noise?

39:33.320 --> 39:35.276
My dogs will be having their nap.

39:35.400 --> 39:37.277
Nice doggy.

39:37.400 --> 39:38.515
Nice... doggy.

39:38.800 --> 39:40.756
<i>(snarling)</i>

39:56.080 --> 39:57.593
Otto, what are you doing?

39:57.720 --> 40:00.154
It's a Buddhist meditation technique.

40:00.280 --> 40:02.157
It focuses your aggression.

40:02.280 --> 40:04.919
The monks did it
before they went into battle.

40:05.040 --> 40:06.996
What kind of Buddhism is this?

40:08.680 --> 40:09.635
<i>(honks horn)</i>

40:10.560 --> 40:11.515
<i>(crashing)</i>

40:11.640 --> 40:13.153
Asshole!

40:14.080 --> 40:16.355
It's an early Tantric meditation...

40:16.480 --> 40:17.799
What is this?

40:17.920 --> 40:21.708
To get information,
I might have to get friendly with him.

40:21.840 --> 40:24.434
Well, we're ready now, at last.

40:24.560 --> 40:26.516
Good. Enjoy the opera, darling.

40:26.640 --> 40:29.359
- Your supper's in the fridge.
- Marvellous.

40:29.480 --> 40:30.435
Be good.

40:31.240 --> 40:34.710
When you say friendly,
what are we talking about here?

40:34.840 --> 40:36.637
